page.title: 11M25 Motorway
page.content: Through the centre of our Domesday grid,like a slithering snake,the M25 runs from the Swanley interchange due north to the Dartford Tunnel.This section of the M25 is part of the orbital motorway that when completed will encircle London like a huge roundabout.Roads,a railway line,and footbridge cross the motorway.Button St ,runing beneath the M25 tunnel as vehicles zoom overhead. By Rams Wood the railway line,almost unseen,passes beneath the M25 linking Swanley to the Medway towns.Ship Lane, from Swanley Village to Sutton-at-Hone almost hidden passes under the motorway .Not until the bridge at Clement St does a structure span the motorway itself.Further due north along the motorway an attractive footbridge,with spiral staircases, spans the motorway.
